The paper deals with the problem of a robot learning the mechanical properties of objects through physical interaction, which is a core problem in robotics. The proposed method utilizes a physics engine, which is a common tool in robotics for simulating physical interactions. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a data-efficient approach for identifying the motion models of objects, which involves Bayesian optimization, a popular machine learning technique. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves policy search, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper includes experimental results using a real robot, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the robot uses vision to perceive the object.
